TITLE: Configuring Recommended Strategy with Limit and Idle Timeout (HOCON)
DESCRIPTION: This HOCON configuration combines the recommended default passivation strategy with an active entity limit of 100,000 and also enables idle entity passivation. Entities will be passivated if the active limit is reached OR if they remain idle for the specified `idle-timeout` (defaulting to 2 minutes if not explicitly set elsewhere).
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/cluster-sharding.md#2025-04-22_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: hocon
CODE:
```
akka.cluster.sharding {
  passivation {
    strategy = default-strategy
    default-strategy {
      # approximately 100k entities per node
      limit = 100000
      # also passivate entities that have been idle for 10 minutes
      idle-entity {
        timeout = 10 minutes
      }
    }
  }
}
```

