TITLE: Broadcasting Akka Streams with GraphDSL in Java
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates building a non-linear stream graph using `GraphDSL` in Java to broadcast elements from a single source (`tweets`) to multiple sinks (`writeAuthors` and `writeHashtags`). It explicitly uses the graph builder (`b`) and methods like `add()`, `from()`, `via()`, and `to()` to define the stream topology with a `Broadcast` junction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-quickstart.md#2025-04-22_snippet_35

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
RunnableGraph.fromGraph(GraphDSL.create(b -> {
  final UniformFanOutShape<Tweet, Tweet> bcast = b.add(Broadcast.create(2));
  b.from(tweets).toInlet(bcast.in());
  b.from(bcast.out(0)).via(Flow.of(Tweet.class).map(t -> t.author)).to(writeAuthors);
  b.from(bcast.out(1)).via(Flow.of(Tweet.class).mapConcat(t -> new ArrayList<>(t.getHashtags()))).to(writeHashtags);
  return ClosedShape.getInstance();
})).run(materializer);
