TITLE: Sorting Elements to Multiple Groups with groupBy in Akka Streams
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of the multi-group pattern that maps messages to multiple topics and creates separate streams for each topic. It uses mapConcat to flatten the message-topic pairs and groupBy to create topic-specific streams.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-cookbook.md#2025-04-22_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
// For every topic, a separate group of elements:
Source.single(new Message())
    .mapConcat(
        (msg) -> {
          // Get the topics a message belongs to
          List<String> topics = topicMapper(msg);
          // Create a group for each topic
          return topics.stream()
              .map((topic) -> new Pair<>(msg, topic))
              .collect(Collectors.toList());
        })
    // now we group by the topic, which gives us a separate substream for each topic
    .groupBy(maxTopics, pair -> pair.second())
    // from each Message-Topic pair we only are interested in the Message
    .map(pair -> pair.first())
```

