TITLE: Implementing a Persistent Actor in Java
DESCRIPTION: Example of a Java implementation of an AbstractPersistentActor that demonstrates event sourcing pattern. The actor persists events, recovers state from events, and handles commands by generating and persisting events.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/persistence.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
class ExamplePersistentActor extends AbstractPersistentActor {

  private ExampleState state = new ExampleState();

  @Override
  public String persistenceId() {
    return "sample-id-1";
  }

  @Override
  public Receive createReceiveRecover() {
    return receiveBuilder()
      .match(Evt.class, this::updateState)
      .match(
          SnapshotOffer.class,
          ss -> this.state = (ExampleState) ss.snapshot())
      .build();
  }

  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
      .match(
          Cmd.class,
          cmd -> {
            final Evt evt = new Evt(cmd.getData());
            persist(
                evt,
                (Evt e) -> {
                  updateState(e);
                  getContext().getSystem().getEventStream().publish(e);
                  if (lastSequenceNr() % 1000 == 0) saveSnapshot(state);
                });
          })
      .matchEquals("snap", s -> saveSnapshot(state))
      .match(SaveSnapshotSuccess.class, s -> {})
      .match(SaveSnapshotFailure.class, f -> {})
      .build();
  }

  private void updateState(Evt evt) {
    state = state.updated(evt);
  }
}
```

