DESCRIPTION: Provides the Scala implementation of the `commandHandler` for the counter example. It pattern matches on the incoming `Command` and returns the appropriate `Effect`: `persist` for state changes (`Increment`, `IncrementBy`) and `none` for read-only operations (`GetValue`), potentially chaining a `thenReply` side effect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/durable-state/persistence.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
import akka.persistence.typed.scaladsl.Effect

val commandHandler: (State, Command) => Effect[State] = {
  (state, command) =>
    command match {
      case Increment =>
        Effect.persist(State(state.value + 1))
      case IncrementBy(value) =>
        Effect.persist(State(state.value + value))
      case GetValue(replyTo) =>
        Effect.none.thenReply(replyTo)(s => s)
    }
}
```

