TITLE: Balancing Jobs to a Fixed Pool of Workers in Akka Streams
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of the worker pool pattern that distributes jobs to a configurable number of parallel workers. It creates a balanced processing flow that handles work distribution and result merging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-cookbook.md#2025-04-22_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public static <In, Out> Flow<In, Out, NotUsed> balancer(
    Flow<In, Out, NotUsed> worker, int workerCount) {
  return Flow.fromGraph(
      GraphDSL.create(
          b -> {
            final Outlet<In> balancerOut = b.add(Balance.<In>create(workerCount, false)).out(0);
            final UniformFanInShape<Out, Out> mergeIn = b.add(Merge.<Out>create(workerCount));

            for (int i = 0; i < workerCount; i++) {
              final FlowShape<In, Out> workerFlow = b.add(worker.async());
              b.from(balancerOut).viaFanOut(b.add(Balance.<In>create(workerCount, false))).toInlet(workerFlow.in());
              b.from(workerFlow.out()).toInlet(mergeIn.in(i));
            }

            return new FlowShape<>(balancerOut, mergeIn.out());
          }));
}
```

