TITLE: Implementing Adhoc Source in Akka Streams
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of the adhoc source pattern that creates a source that starts on demand and shuts down when there's no demand. It handles backpressure timeouts and automatically recovers by creating a new source when needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-cookbook.md#2025-04-22_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
// Imports
import akka.stream.javadsl.Source;
import akka.stream.javadsl.Flow;
import java.time.Duration;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException;

// We need some recursive type here because adhocSource uses adhocSource
Source<TwitterDocument, NotUsed> adhocSource =
    Source.repeat(1)
        .map(n -> readTwitter())
        // The lazy source, emits when there is demand
        .via(Flow.lazyCompletionStageFlow(() -> createAdhocFlow()))
        // If there was no demand for 5 seconds, complete
        .backpressureTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(5))
        // If we got completion from upstream, just start over when there is demand again
        .recoverWithRetries(
            1,
            new PFBuilder<Throwable, Source<TwitterDocument, NotUsed>>()
                .match(
                    TimeoutException.class,
                    ex -> adhocSource) // Recursive reference here
                .build());
```

