SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/RetryFlow/withBackoffAndContext.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
val flow: FlowWithContext[Int, SomeContext, Int, SomeContext, NotUsed] =
  // business logic
  FlowWithContext[Int, SomeContext].map { i =>
    i - 1
  }

val retryFlow: FlowWithContext[Int, SomeContext, Int, SomeContext, NotUsed] =
  RetryFlow.withBackoffAndContext(minBackoff = 10.millis, maxBackoff = 5.seconds, randomFactor = 0.2, maxRetries = 3, flow =
    flow) {
    case ((in, ctx), (out, _)) =>
      if (out <= 0) None // do not retry on 0 or negative
      else if (in - 1 == out) None // do not retry on expected outcome
      else Some((in, ctx)) // otherwise retry with the original value
  }
```

