TITLE: Creating a Balanced and Live Cycle with Initial Element in Akka Streams (Java)
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of a balanced cycle that injects an initial element using Concat. This solves the chicken-and-egg problem by providing an independent initial element that kicks off the cycle, allowing it to process elements continuously without deadlock.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-graphs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
final RunnableGraph<NotUsed> zippingLive =
    RunnableGraph.fromGraph(
        GraphDSL.create(
            b -> {
              final FanInShape2<Integer, Integer, Integer> zip =
                  b.add(ZipWith.create((Integer left, Integer right) -> right));
              final UniformFanOutShape<Integer, Integer> bcast = b.add(Broadcast.create(2));
              final UniformFanInShape<Integer, Integer> concat = b.add(Concat.create(2));

              b.from(b.add(source)).toInlet(zip.in0());
              b.from(zip.out())
                  .via(b.add(Flow.of(Integer.class).map(s -> { System.out.println(s); return s; })))
                  .viaFanOut(bcast)
                  .to(b.add(Sink.ignore()));

              b.from(b.add(Source.single(0))).toFanIn(concat);
              b.from(bcast).toFanIn(concat);
              b.from(concat).toInlet(zip.in1());

              return ClosedShape.getInstance();
            }));
```

