TITLE: Implementing Duplicate Transformation with GraphStage in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the Java implementation of a one-to-many operator using GraphStage. It creates a duplicate operator that emits each upstream element twice downstream, demonstrating state management within the operator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-customize.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class Duplicator<A> extends GraphStage<FlowShape<A, A>> {
  private final Inlet<A> in = Inlet.create("Duplicator.in");
  private final Outlet<A> out = Outlet.create("Duplicator.out");

  private final FlowShape<A, A> shape = FlowShape.of(in, out);

  @Override
  public FlowShape<A, A> shape() {
    return shape;
  }

  @Override
  public GraphStageLogic createLogic(Attributes inheritedAttributes) {
    return new GraphStageLogic(shape) {
      private boolean seen = false;

      private void maybePull() {
        if (!seen) pull(in);
      }

      {
        setHandler(
            in,
            new AbstractInHandler() {
              @Override
              public void onPush() {
                A elem = grab(in);
                seen = true;
                push(out, elem);
              }

              @Override
              public void onUpstreamFinish() {
                if (!seen) completeStage();
                else {
                  // There is an element buffered, let it be sent downstream
                  // before completion
                }
              }
            });
        setHandler(
            out,
            new AbstractOutHandler() {
              @Override
              public void onPull() {
                if (isClosed(in)) {
                  if (seen) {
                    // We're done
                    completeStage();
                  } // else onUpstreamFinish completed us
                } else if (seen) {
                  seen = false;
                  push(out, grab(in));
                } else {
                  maybePull();
                }
              }
            });
      }
    };
  }
}
```

