TITLE: Defining a Simple Echo Handler Actor in Java
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet defines a `SimpleEchoHandler` actor responsible for handling a single TCP connection. It implements an echo server logic with ACK-based back-pressure: it receives data (`Tcp.Received`), buffers it, writes it back using `TcpMessage.write` with a custom `Ack` event, and waits for the `Ack` before sending subsequent data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class SimpleEchoHandler extends AbstractActor {

  private final LoggingAdapter log = Logging.getLogger(getContext().system(), this);

  private final ActorRef connection;
  private final Vector<ByteString> storage = new Vector<>();
  private long stored = 0L;
  private long transferred = 0L;
  private static final long maxStored = 100000000L;
  private boolean closed = false;
  private int nextAck = 1;

  public static Props props(ActorRef connection) {
    return Props.create(SimpleEchoHandler.class, connection);
  }

  // this is the ACK object explained in the docs
  public static final class Ack implements Tcp.Event {
    private final int ack;

    public Ack(int ack) {
      this.ack = ack;
    }

    public static Ack create(int ack) {
      return new Ack(ack);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
      if (this == o) return true;
      if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;
      Ack ack1 = (Ack) o;
      return ack == ack1.ack;
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
      return Objects.hash(ack);
    }

    @Override
    public String toString() {
      return "Ack(" + ack + ')';
    }
  }

  public SimpleEchoHandler(ActorRef connection) {
    this.connection = connection;

    // sign death pact: this actor stops when the connection is closed
    getContext().watch(connection);

    connection.tell(TcpMessage.resumeReading(), getSelf());
  }

  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
        .match(
            Tcp.Received.class,
            data -> {
              buffer(data.data());
            })
        .match(
            Ack.class,
            ack -> {
              acknowledge(ack.ack);
            })
        .match(
            Tcp.ConnectionClosed.class,
            closed -> {
              if (storage.isEmpty()) {
                getContext().stop(getSelf());
              } else {
                getContext().become(closing());
              }
            })
        .build();
  }
}
```

