TITLE: Initiating Manual Passivation in an Akka Entity (Scala)
DESCRIPTION: This Scala code demonstrates how an entity actor can initiate its own passivation process. It sends a `ClusterSharding.Passivate` message to its parent shard, specifying a `GoodByeCounter` message to be sent back to itself as a signal to stop. This allows for graceful shutdown and prevents message loss.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/cluster-sharding.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
case class GoodByeCounter(id: String) extends CounterCommand

val counterActor = Behaviors.receiveMessage[CounterCommand] { cmd =>
  cmd match {
    case Increment =>
      println(s"Counter ${context.self.path.name} incremented")
      Behaviors.same
    case GetValue(replyTo) =>
      replyTo ! 42
      Behaviors.same
    case PassivateCounter =>
      context.log.info("Passivating")
      shard ! ClusterSharding.Passivate(context.self)
      Behaviors.same
    case GoodByeCounter(_) =>
      // can do cleanup here, then stop
      Behaviors.stopped
  }
}
```

