TITLE: Implementing Echo Handler with NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Scala
DESCRIPTION: A Scala implementation of an EchoHandler that uses NACK-based write back-pressure. It processes incoming TCP data and writes it back, handling command failures appropriately.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
class EchoHandler(connection: ActorRef) extends Actor {  
  import Tcp._
  implicit val byteOrder: ByteOrder = ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN

  // sign death pact: this actor terminates when connection breaks
  context.watch(connection)

  case object Ack extends Event

  def receive: Receive = writing

  def writing: Receive = {
    case Received(data) =>
      connection ! Write(data, Ack)
      context.become(buffering(Vector.empty[ByteString]))

    case _: ConnectionClosed =>
      context.stop(self)
  }
```

