TITLE: Implementing Generic Reduce-by-Key in Akka Streams
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of the generalized reduce-by-key pattern that provides a reusable solution for aggregating elements by key. It separates the concerns of grouping, mapping, and reducing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-cookbook.md#2025-04-22_snippet_27

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public static <In, K, Out> Flow<In, Pair<K, Out>, NotUsed> reduceByKey(
    int maximumGroupSize,
    Function<In, K> groupKey,
    Function<In, Out> map,
    BiFunction<Out, Out, Out> reduce) {
  return Flow.<In>create()
      .groupBy(maximumGroupSize, groupKey::apply)
      .map(el -> new Pair<>(groupKey.apply(el), map.apply(el)))
      .reduce(
          (left, right) -> new Pair<>(left.first(), reduce.apply(left.second(), right.second())))
      .mergeSubstreams();
}
```

