TITLE: Sending Elements to Typed Actor With Backpressure Using Akka Streams (Java)
DESCRIPTION: This Java example illustrates pushing elements from an Akka Stream to a typed ActorRef using actorRefWithBackpressure, where each element triggers an acknowledgement mechanism to implement backpressure. Prerequisites include akka-actor-typed, akka-stream-typed, and a properly initialized ActorSystem. It demonstrates supplying the actor reference, lambda functions for message adaptation, initialization, completion and failure message handling. The Sink created will only pull new elements when the actor acknowledges readiness.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/ActorSink/actorRefWithBackpressure.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
import akka.actor.typed.ActorRef;
import akka.stream.javadsl.Sink;
import akka.stream.typed.javadsl.ActorSink;
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage;

interface Command {}
class Element implements Command {
  public final String value;
  public final ActorRef<Ack> replyTo;
  public Element(String value, ActorRef<Ack> replyTo) { this.value = value; this.replyTo = replyTo; }
}
class Init implements Command {}
class Complete implements Command {}
class Fail implements Command {
  public final Throwable ex;
  public Fail(Throwable ex) { this.ex = ex; }
}
class Ack {}

ActorRef<Command> actor = ...; // Acquired from system

Sink<String, akka.NotUsed> sink = ActorSink.actorRefWithBackpressure(
  actor,
  (replyTo, elem) -> new Element(elem, replyTo),
  replyTo -> new Init(),
  new Ack(),
  new Complete(),
  ex -> new Fail(ex)
);

a.List.of("a", "b", "c").stream().runWith(sink, system)
```

