TITLE: Implementing Custom TwoPhaseSet in Java
DESCRIPTION: Example of implementing a custom TwoPhaseSet data type in Java. It shows how to create a CRDT that allows adding and removing elements, but never adding an element again after removal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/distributed-data.md#2025-04-22_snippet_27

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class TwoPhaseSet extends AbstractReplicatedData<TwoPhaseSet> {
  private final GSet<String> adds;
  private final GSet<String> removes;

  public TwoPhaseSet() {
    this(GSet.create(), GSet.create());
  }

  private TwoPhaseSet(GSet<String> adds, GSet<String> removes) {
    this.adds = adds;
    this.removes = removes;
  }

  public TwoPhaseSet add(String element) {
    return new TwoPhaseSet(adds.add(element), removes);
  }

  public TwoPhaseSet remove(String element) {
    return new TwoPhaseSet(adds, removes.add(element));
  }

  public boolean contains(String element) {
    return adds.contains(element) && !removes.contains(element);
  }

  @Override
  public TwoPhaseSet mergeData(TwoPhaseSet other) {
    return new TwoPhaseSet(adds.merge(other.adds), removes.merge(other.removes));
  }
}
```

