TITLE: Initiating Manual Passivation in an Akka Entity (Java)
DESCRIPTION: This Java code demonstrates how an entity actor can initiate its own passivation. It sends a `ClusterSharding.Passivate` message containing a reference to itself to the shard actor. A custom stop message, `GoodByeCounter`, is defined and expected to be received before the actor stops itself, allowing for cleanup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/cluster-sharding.md#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
static class GoodByeCounter implements CounterCommand {
  private final String id;

  GoodByeCounter(String id) {
    this.id = id;
  }
}

Behavior<CounterCommand> counter(ActorRef<ClusterSharding.ShardCommand> shard, String entityId) {
  return Behaviors.receive(CounterCommand.class)
      .onMessage(
          Increment.class,
          (context, cmd) -> {
            context.getLog().info("Counter {} incremented", entityId);
            return Behaviors.same();
          })
      .onMessage(
          GetValue.class,
          (context, cmd) -> {
            cmd.replyTo.tell(42);
            return Behaviors.same();
          })
      .onMessage(
          PassivateCounter.class,
          (context, cmd) -> {
            context.getLog().info("Passivating counter {}", entityId);
            shard.tell(new ClusterSharding.Passivate<>(context.getSelf()));
            return Behaviors.same();
          })
      .onMessage(
          GoodByeCounter.class,
          (context, cmd) -> {
            // can do cleanup here
            context.getLog().info("Counter {} stopped", entityId);
            return Behaviors.stopped();
          })
      .build();
}
```

