DESCRIPTION: This Scala snippet demonstrates forwarding elements from an Akka Stream to a typed actor using the actorRefWithBackpressure sink operator, enabling explicit backpressure handling through acknowledgement messages. Dependencies include akka-actor-typed and akka-stream-typed; example requires a configured ActorSystem. Key parameters are the target ActorRef, message adapter for stream-to-actor translation, functions to set up handshake/init, message to signal completion, and how to handle errors. Output is a Sink for stream materialization with demand controlled by the actor.
