TITLE: Connection Closing Handler for NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Java
DESCRIPTION: The closing state of the Java EchoHandler that manages graceful TCP connection shutdown while ensuring all buffered data is sent. It handles write command failures during the closing process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private Receive closing(final Tcp.ConnectionClosed reason, final List<ByteString> buffer) {
  return receiveBuilder()
      .match(
          Tcp.CommandFailed.class,
          msg -> {
            connection.tell(TcpMessage.resumeWriting(), getSelf());
            return waitingForAckAndClosing(reason, buffer);
          })
      .match(
          Ack.class,
          msg -> {
            if (buffer.isEmpty()) {
              getContext().stop(getSelf());
              return Stay();
            } else {
              connection.tell(
                  TcpMessage.write(buffer.remove(0), Ack.getInstance()), getSelf());
              return closing(reason, buffer);
            }
          })
      .build();
}
```

