TITLE: Creating Reactive Streams Publishers with Sink.asPublisher in Java
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a Publisher from a Sink in Java using both fanout=true to allow multiple subscribers and fanout=false to restrict to a single subscriber.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Sink/asPublisher.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
final Source<Integer, NotUsed> source = Source.range(1, 5);

// When fanout is set to true, the Sink can support multiple subscribers
final Pair<NotUsed, Publisher<Integer>> publisherPairWithFanout =
    source.toMat(Sink.asPublisher(AsPublisher.WITH_FANOUT), Keep.both()).run(system);

publisherPairWithFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-A"));
publisherPairWithFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-B"));
publisherPairWithFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-C"));

// expect 5 elements for each of the three subscribers

// When fanout is set to false, the first subscriber will receive the elements
// and the rest will be rejected
final Pair<NotUsed, Publisher<Integer>> publisherPairWithoutFanout =
    source.toMat(Sink.asPublisher(AsPublisher.WITHOUT_FANOUT), Keep.both()).run(system);

publisherPairWithoutFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-A"));
publisherPairWithoutFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-B")); // will receive onError
publisherPairWithoutFanout.second().subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-C")); // will receive onError

// expect 5 elements for subscriber "WithoutFanout-A", but error for "WithoutFanout-B/C"
```

