TITLE: Sending Messages with askWithStatus Operator (Akka Streams, Java)
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet illustrates how to use the ActorFlow.askWithStatus method in Akka Streams to send elements in a Java stream to a typed actor and handle typed StatusReply responses. Dependency on Akka Stream Typed and Typed libraries is required, along with configuration of the Akka library repository for Maven or Gradle. The code involves supplying the target actor ref, timeout, parallelism, and a BiFunction to create the message expecting a reply. Inputs are stream elements; outputs are unwrapped statuses, e.g., Strings. The stream may fail on ask timeout or actor termination. Inputs and outputs are strongly typed, and generic parameters are used for maximum flexibility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/ActorFlow/askWithStatus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
import akka.actor.typed.ActorRef;
import akka.pattern.StatusReply;
import akka.stream.javadsl.Flow;
import akka.stream.javadsl.Sink;
import akka.stream.javadsl.Source;
import java.time.Duration;

// Actor message definition
class AskingWithStatus {
  public final ActorRef<StatusReply<String>> replyTo;
  public AskingWithStatus(ActorRef<StatusReply<String>> replyTo) {
    this.replyTo = replyTo;
  }
}

ActorRef<AskingWithStatus> actorRef = ...;
Duration timeout = Duration.ofSeconds(3);
int parallelism = 5;

Flow<Object, String, akka.NotUsed> flow =
  akka.stream.typed.javadsl.ActorFlow.askWithStatus(
      parallelism,
      actorRef,
      timeout,
      (in, replyTo) -> new AskingWithStatus(replyTo)
  );

// Usage in a stream:
Source.single("start-request")
      .via(flow)
      .runWith(Sink.foreach(System.out::println), actorSystem);
```

