TITLE: Implementing Subchannel Classification Bus in Java
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of an EventBus using Subchannel Classification. It demonstrates hierarchical event classification and publishing based on topic hierarchies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class SubchannelBusImpl extends EventBus<MsgEnvelope, String, ActorRef>
    implements SubchannelClassification {
  // Subclassification means that subscribers won't get messages with
  // a classifier that is more specific than what they have subscribed to
  @Override
  public String classify(MsgEnvelope event) {
    return event.topic;
  }

  // Topic can be freely defined by the publisher
  // Subscribers receive messages if the topic is equal or a parent of
  // what they have subscribed to
  @Override
  public Subclassification<String> subclassification() {
    return new Subclassification<String>() {
      @Override
      public boolean isEqual(String x, String y) {
        return x.equals(y);
      }

      @Override
      public boolean isSubclass(String x, String y) {
        return x.startsWith(y);
      }
    };
  }

  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers which registered themselves
  // for the event's classifier
  @Override
  public void publish(MsgEnvelope event, ActorRef subscriber) {
    subscriber.tell(event.payload, ActorRef.noSender());
  }

  // may define the subscriber order which is used throughout the lifetime of the EventBus
  @Override
  public int compareSubscribers(ActorRef a, ActorRef b) {
    return a.compareTo(b);
  }

  // determines the initial size of the index data structure
  // used internally (i.e. the expected number of different classifiers)
  @Override
  public int mapSize() {
    return 128;
  }
}
```

