TITLE: Implementing Custom Failure Counting in Akka CircuitBreaker (Scala)
DESCRIPTION: This Scala example demonstrates how to define custom failure criteria for a circuit breaker by treating even numbers as failures, regardless of whether the operation succeeds or fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/common/circuitbreaker.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
// We define a function that will determine whether to count the result as a failure.
// In this example, we treat even numbers as failure, regardless whether
// the operation succeeded or not
def defineEvenNumberAsFailure[T]: Try[T] => Boolean = {
  case Success(i: Int) => i % 2 == 0
  case Success(_)      => false
  case Failure(_)      => true
}

val circuitBreaker = CircuitBreaker.create(
  system.scheduler,
  maxFailures = 1,
  callTimeout = 1.second,
  resetTimeout = 1.second)

// Wrapping a future, defining even numbers as failure
val oddAndEvenNumbers = Vector(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)

val futures = oddAndEvenNumbers.map(n => {
  circuitBreaker.withCircuitBreaker(
    Future {
      Thread.sleep(10)
      n
    },
    defineEvenNumberAsFailure
  )
})
```

