TITLE: Implementing a Subscriber Actor in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of a subscriber actor that registers for a specific topic with the DistributedPubSubMediator. The actor joins the 'content' topic and handles received messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/distributed-pub-sub.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
static class Subscriber extends AbstractActor {
  String id = self().path().name();
  ActorRef mediator = DistributedPubSub.get(getContext().getSystem()).mediator();

  @Override
  public void preStart() {
    // subscribe to the topic named "content"
    mediator.tell(new Subscribe("content", self()), self());
  }

  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
        .match(
            SubscribeAck.class,
            msg -> msg.subscribe().topic().equals("content") && msg.subscribe().ref().equals(self()),
            s -> getContext().become(ready()))
        .build();
  }

  private Receive ready() {
    return receiveBuilder().matchAny(msg -> System.out.println("Got: " + msg)).build();
  }
}
```

