TITLE: Implementing Movies Watch List with ORSet CRDT in Java
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of a movies watch list using Observed Remove Set (ORSet) CRDT in Java. The implementation demonstrates handling concurrent add/remove operations with automatic conflict resolution where add wins over remove.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/replicated-eventsourcing.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class MovieWatchList {
  private final String userId;
  private final ORSet<String> movies;

  public MovieWatchList(String userId, ORSet<String> movies) {
    this.userId = userId;
    this.movies = movies;
  }

  public MovieWatchList(String userId) {
    this(userId, ORSet.empty());
  }

  public MovieWatchList add(String movieId) {
    return new MovieWatchList(userId, movies.add(ReplicaId.random(), movieId));
  }

  public MovieWatchList remove(String movieId) {
    return new MovieWatchList(userId, movies.remove(movieId));
  }

  public boolean contains(String movieId) {
    return movies.getElements().contains(movieId);
  }
}
```

