TITLE: Buffer Until Changed Pattern in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation that buffers elements until the incoming element changes, then emits the buffered elements downstream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Source-or-Flow/statefulMap.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
Source.from(Arrays.asList(1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3))
    .statefulMap(
        () -> new Pair<>(new ArrayList<Integer>(), Optional.empty()),
        (Pair<ArrayList<Integer>, Optional<Integer>> state, Integer element) -> {
          ArrayList<Integer> buffer = state.first();
          Optional<Integer> prev = state.second();
          if (prev.isPresent() && prev.get().equals(element)) {
            buffer.add(element);
            return new Pair<>(
                new Pair<>(buffer, prev),
                new ArrayList<Integer>());
          } else {
            ArrayList<Integer> emitBuffer = buffer;
            ArrayList<Integer> newBuffer = new ArrayList<>();
            newBuffer.add(element);
            return new Pair<>(
                new Pair<>(newBuffer, Optional.of(element)),
                emitBuffer);
          }
        },
        state -> Optional.of(state.first()));
```

