TITLE: Using Broadcast to Aggregate Stream Values in Scala
DESCRIPTION: This Scala snippet demonstrates the basic usage of `Broadcast(2)` to split a stream of integers. One output flow calculates the sum using `fold`, and the other calculates the count using `fold`. The results from both flows are then combined using `Zip` and printed to the console.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Broadcast.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
val source = Source(1 to 10)

val graph = RunnableGraph.fromGraph(GraphDSL.create() { implicit builder =>
  import GraphDSL.Implicits._

  val broadcast = builder.add(Broadcast[Int](2))
  val merge = builder.add(Zip[BigInt, Int]())

  val sumSink = Sink.fold[BigInt, Int](0)(_ + _)
  val countSink = Sink.fold[Int, Int](0)((c, _) => c + 1)

source ~> broadcast

  broadcast.out(0) ~> Flow[Int].map(BigInt(_)) ~> merge.in0
  broadcast.out(1) ~> merge.in1

  merge.out ~> Sink.foreach(println)

  ClosedShape
})

graph.run()
```

