TITLE: Connection Closing Handler for NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Scala
DESCRIPTION: The closing state of the Scala EchoHandler that manages the graceful shutdown of a TCP connection while ensuring all data is sent. It handles command failures during the closing process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def closing(reason: ConnectionClosed, buffer: Vector[ByteString]): Receive = {
  case CommandFailed(Write(_, Ack)) =>
    connection ! ResumeWriting
    context.become(waitingForAckAndClosing(reason, buffer))

  case Ack =>
    if (buffer.isEmpty) {
      context.stop(self)
    } else {
      connection ! Write(buffer.head, Ack)
      context.become(closing(reason, buffer.tail))
    }
}
```

