TITLE: Checking Recovery Status within a Persistent Actor (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how an AbstractPersistentActor can check if the recovery process is currently active using the `isRecoveryRunning()` method. Additionally, it demonstrates retrieving the sequence number of the most recently replayed event via `recoveryRunningNum()`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/persistence.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override
public Receive createReceiveRecover() {
  return receiveBuilder()
      .match(Evt.class, this::updateState)
      .match(SnapshotOffer.class, ss -> state = (State) ss.snapshot())
      .match(RecoveryCompleted.class, this::onRecoveryComplete)
      .build();
}

private void onRecoveryComplete(RecoveryCompleted completed) {
  log().info(
      "MyPersistentActor [{}] recovery completed. Current state: [{}]", persistenceId(), state);
}

@Override
public Receive createReceive() {
  return receiveBuilder()
      .matchEquals(GetState.class, s -> sender().tell(state, self()))
      .matchEquals("snap", s -> saveSnapshot(state))
      .matchEquals(
          "print",
          s -> {
            log().info(
                "MyPersistentActor [{}] received [print] command. Current state: [{}]",
                persistenceId(),
                state);
            if (isRecoveryRunning()) {
              log().info("RECOVERY RUNNING: " + recoveryRunningNum());
            } else {
              log().info("RECOVERY COMPLETED");
            }
          })
      .match(
          SaveUser.class,
          save ->
              persist(
                  new UserSaved(save.getUser()),
                  (UserSaved evt) -> {
                    updateState(evt);
                  }))
      .build();
}
```

