TITLE: Handling Buffering for NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Scala
DESCRIPTION: The buffering state of the Scala EchoHandler that manages write failures. It buffers data while writing is suspended and resumes when TCP connection is ready to accept more writes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def buffering(buffer: Vector[ByteString]): Receive = {
  case Received(data) =>
    connection ! Write(data, Ack)
    context.become(buffering(buffer :+ data))

  case CommandFailed(Write(_, Ack)) =>
    connection ! ResumeWriting
    context.become(waitingForAck(buffer))

  case Ack =>
    if (buffer.isEmpty) {
      context.become(writing)
    } else {
      connection ! Write(buffer.head, Ack)
      context.become(buffering(buffer.tail))
    }

  case _: ConnectionClosed =>
    context.stop(self)
}
```

