TITLE: Registering Actor DeathWatch Monitoring in Akka (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to register a Java Akka actor to watch another actor for Terminated messages via DeathWatch. Requires Akka libraries, actor references, and appropriate imports. The snippet includes both relevant import of Terminated and usage of context().watch(target), allowing actors to observe and respond to the lifecycle end of peer actors. Input is the ActorRef to be watched; output is handling of Terminated messages when the target actor is stopped or terminated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/actors.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: java
