TITLE: Deferred Stream Creation Based on Initial Element in Java
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a deferred stream based on the initial element by combining completionStageFlow with prefixAndTail in Akka Streams.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Flow/completionStageFlow.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
Source.from(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3))
    .prefixAndTail(1)
    .flatMapConcat(
        (pair) -> {
          Integer firstElement = pair.first().get(0);
          Source<Integer> tail = pair.second();

          CompletionStage<Flow<Integer, Integer, NotUsed>> futureFlow =
              CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(
                  () -> {
                    // create a different flow based on the first element
                    if (firstElement % 2 == 0) {
                      return Flow.of(Integer.class).map(i -> i * 2);
                    } else {
                      return Flow.of(Integer.class).map(i -> i + 1);
                    }
                  });

          return tail.via(Flow.completionStageFlow(futureFlow));
        })
    .runWith(Sink.foreach(System.out::println), system);
```

