TITLE: Implementing Command Handler for Blog Post Entity (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Implements the command handler for a blog post entity using a CommandHandlerBuilder in Java.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/persistence.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
private CommandHandlerBuilder<Command, Event, State> commandHandler() {
  return newCommandHandlerBuilder()
      .forStateType(EmptyState.class)
      .onCommand(AddPost.class, this::onAddPost)
      .forStateType(DraftState.class)
      .onCommand(GetPost.class, this::onGetPost)
      .onCommand(ChangeBody.class, this::onChangeBody)
      .onCommand(Publish.class, this::onPublish)
      .forStateType(PublishedState.class)
      .onCommand(GetPost.class, this::onGetPost)
      .onCommand(AddComment.class, this::onAddComment)
      .orElse(newCommandHandlerBuilder().onAnyCommand(() -> Effect().unhandled()));
}

private Effect<Event, State> onAddPost(EmptyState state, AddPost command) {
  return Effect().persist(new PostAdded(command.content));
}

private Effect<Event, State> onGetPost(DraftState state, GetPost command) {
  command.replyTo.tell(state.content);
  return Effect().none();
}

private Effect<Event, State> onChangeBody(DraftState state, ChangeBody command) {
  return Effect().persist(new BodyChanged(command.newBody));
}

private Effect<Event, State> onPublish(DraftState state, Publish command) {
  return Effect().persist(PostPublished.INSTANCE);
}

private Effect<Event, State> onGetPost(PublishedState state, GetPost command) {
  command.replyTo.tell(state.content);
  return Effect().none();
}

private Effect<Event, State> onAddComment(PublishedState state, AddComment command) {
  return Effect().persist(new CommentAdded(command.user, command.comment));
}
```

