TITLE: Implementing Compression for TwoPhaseSet Serialization in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java example showing how to add Gzip compression to a serializer using the AbstractSerializationSupport interface, which can reduce data size for network transmission.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/distributed-data.md#2025-04-22_snippet_34

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override
public byte[] toBinary(Object o) {
  if (o instanceof TwoPhaseSet) {
    TwoPhaseSetMessages.TwoPhaseSet msg = twoPhaseSetToProto((TwoPhaseSet) o);
    return compress(msg.toByteArray());
  } else
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Can't serialize object of type " + o.getClass());
}

@Override
public Object fromBinary(byte[] bytes, String manifest) {
  if (TWOPHASESET_MANIFEST.equals(manifest))
    return twoPhaseSetFromBinary(uncompress(bytes));
  else
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("Unknown manifest: " + manifest);
}
```

