TITLE: Declaring Messages in Static Classes in Java
DESCRIPTION: Best practice for declaring message types that an actor can receive as static classes inside the Actor class for better code organization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/actors.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class WatchActor extends AbstractActor {
  // #messages-in-companion
  // these are the messages our actor handles
  static public class Watch {
    public final ActorRef target;

    public Watch(ActorRef target) {
      this.target = target;
    }
  }

  static public class Transition {
    public final ActorRef target;

    public Transition(ActorRef target) {
      this.target = target;
    }
  }
  // #messages-in-companion

  public static Props props() {
    return Props.create(WatchActor.class, WatchActor::new);
  }

  private final Map<String, ActorRef> watchList = new HashMap<>();

  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
        .match(
            Watch.class,
            w -> {
              ActorRef ref = w.target;
              getContext().watch(ref);
              watchList.put(ref.path().name(), ref);
            })
        .match(
            Transition.class,
            t -> {
              ActorRef ref = t.target;
              getContext().watch(ref);
              watchList.put(ref.path().name(), ref);
            })
        .match(
            Terminated.class,
            t -> {
              ActorRef ref = t.actor();
              String name = ref.path().name();
              if (watchList.get(name) != null) {
                watchList.remove(name);
              }
            })
        .build();
  }
}
```

