TITLE: Implementing Actor Classification Bus in Java
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of an EventBus using Actor Classification, where both events and subscribers are ActorRefs. This pattern is used for implementing DeathWatch in Akka.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class ActorBusImpl extends EventBus<ActorEvent, ActorRef, ActorRef>
    implements ActorClassification {
  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers
  @Override
  public void publish(ActorEvent event, ActorRef subscriber) {
    // in this case event is ActorEvent and subscriber is ActorRef
    if (event.sender.equals(subscriber)) subscriber.tell(event.payload, ActorRef.noSender());
  }

  // may define the subscriber order which is used throughout the lifetime of the EventBus
  @Override
  public int compareSubscribers(ActorRef a, ActorRef b) {
    return a.compareTo(b);
  }

  // determines the initial size of the index data structure
  // used internally (i.e. the expected number of different classifiers)
  @Override
  public int mapSize() {
    return 128;
  }
}
```

