TITLE: Handling Buffering for NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Java
DESCRIPTION: The buffering state of the Java EchoHandler that manages write failures. It buffers data when writing is suspended and resumes writing when the connection is ready to accept more data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private Receive buffering(final List<ByteString> buffer) {
  return receiveBuilder()
      .match(
          Tcp.Received.class,
          msg -> {
            final ByteString data = msg.data();
            buffer.add(data);
            connection.tell(TcpMessage.write(data, Ack.getInstance()), getSelf());
            return this;
          })
      .match(
          Tcp.CommandFailed.class,
          msg -> {
            connection.tell(TcpMessage.resumeWriting(), getSelf());
            return waitingForAck(buffer);
          })
      .match(
          Ack.class,
          msg -> {
            if (buffer.isEmpty()) {
              return createReceive();
            } else {
              connection.tell(
                  TcpMessage.write(buffer.remove(0), Ack.getInstance()), getSelf());
              return buffering(buffer);
            }
          })
      .match(
          Tcp.ConnectionClosed.class,
          msg -> {
            getContext().stop(getSelf());
            return Stay();
          })
      .build();
}
```

