TITLE: Dropping Broadcast in Akka Streams (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of a broadcast that drops elements for slow consumers. Uses buffer with OverflowStrategy.dropHead.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-cookbook.md#2025-04-22_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public Graph<UniformFanOutShape<Integer, Integer>, NotUsed> createDroppyBroadcast() {
    return GraphDSL.create(builder -> {
        final int outputPorts = 2;
        final UniformFanOutShape<Integer, Integer> bcast = builder.add(Broadcast.create(outputPorts));

        final Flow<Integer, Integer, NotUsed> droppyFlow1 =
                Flow.of(Integer.class).buffer(10, OverflowStrategy.dropHead());
        final Flow<Integer, Integer, NotUsed> droppyFlow2 =
                Flow.of(Integer.class).buffer(10, OverflowStrategy.dropHead());

        builder.from(bcast.out(0)).via(builder.add(droppyFlow1));
        builder.from(bcast.out(1)).via(builder.add(droppyFlow2));

        return new UniformFanOutShape<>(bcast.in(), bcast.out(0), bcast.out(1));
    });
}
```

