TITLE: Combining Materialized Values for a Composite Source in Java
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet demonstrates creating a composite Akka Stream `Source`. It combines `source1` (materializing a `CompletableFuture<Optional<Integer>>`) and `source2` using `Source.combine`. The `Keep.left()` combiner function selects the materialized value from `source1` for the resulting `nestedSource`. This allows interaction with the stream component represented by `source1`'s materialized value after the graph runs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-composition.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
// #mat-combine-1
// Source requiring CompletableFuture materialized value
Source<Integer, CompletableFuture<Optional<Integer>>> source1 = Source.maybe();

// Source requiring NotUsed materialized value
Source<Integer, NotUsed> source2 = Source.single(0);

// Combine the sources, picking the CompletableFuture's materialized value
Source<Integer, CompletableFuture<Optional<Integer>>> nestedSource =
    Source.combine(source1, source2, i -> Merge.<Integer>create(i)).named("nestedSource");
// #mat-combine-1
```

