TITLE: Implementing RetryFlow.withBackoff in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use RetryFlow.withBackoff in Java to wrap a flow handling Integers, retrying elements unless the result is 0 or negative, or maxRetries is hit.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/RetryFlow/withBackoff.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
Flow<Integer, Integer, NotUsed> flow =
    Flow.<Integer>create().map(x -> {
      if (x < 5) return x;
      else throw new RuntimeException("x too big");
    });

Flow<Integer, Integer, NotUsed> retryFlow =
    RetryFlow.withBackoff(
        Duration.ofMillis(10),
        Duration.ofSeconds(5),
        0.2,
        5,
        flow,
        (in, out) -> {
          if (out.isSuccess()) {
            Integer result = out.get();
            if (result <= 0) {
              return Optional.empty(); // don't retry on 0 or negative values
            } else {
              return Optional.of(in); // retry on positive values
            }
          } else {
            return Optional.of(in); // retry on failure
          }
        });
```

