TITLE: Implementing Subchannel Classification Bus in Scala
DESCRIPTION: A Scala implementation of an EventBus using Subchannel Classification which allows subscribers to listen to groups of channels. It provides hierarchical event classification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
class SubchannelBusImpl extends
  EventBus[MsgEnvelope, String, ActorRef] with SubchannelClassification {
  // Subclassification means that subscribers won't get messages with
  // a classifier that is more specific than what they have subscribed to
  override protected def classify(event: MsgEnvelope): String = event.topic

  // Topic can be freely defined by the publisher
  // Subscribers receive messages if the topic is equal or a parent of
  // what they have subscribed to
  override protected def subclassification = {
    new Subclassification[String] {
      def isEqual(x: String, y: String) = x == y
      def isSubclass(x: String, y: String) = x.startsWith(y)
    }
  }

  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers which registered themselves
  // for the event's classifier
  override protected def publish(event: MsgEnvelope, subscriber: ActorRef): Unit = {
    subscriber ! event.payload
  }
}
```

