TITLE: Helper Methods for Java Echo Handler (ACK-Based Back-Pressure)
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet provides helper methods for the `SimpleEchoHandler`. The `buffer` method adds incoming data to a storage vector and initiates writing the first chunk if the buffer was empty. The `acknowledge` method removes the acknowledged data chunk from storage and sends the next available chunk, managing the `Ack` sequence number. It also handles suspending/resuming reading based on buffer size and closing the connection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private void buffer(ByteString data) {
    storage.add(data);
    stored += data.size();

    if (stored > maxStored) {
      log.warning("New data {}, total stored: {} exceeds max: {}", data.size(), stored, maxStored);
      connection.tell(TcpMessage.suspendReading(), getSelf());
    }

    if (stored == data.size()) {
      // storage was empty, start writing
      connection.tell(TcpMessage.write(storage.get(0), Ack.create(nextAck)), getSelf());
    }
  }

  private void acknowledge(int ack) {
    assert (!storage.isEmpty());
    assert (ack == nextAck);

    final ByteString acknowledged = storage.get(0);
    final int size = acknowledged.size();

    storage.remove(0);

    stored -= size;
    transferred += size;
    nextAck += 1;

    if (stored < maxStored) {
      connection.tell(TcpMessage.resumeReading(), getSelf());
    }

    if (storage.isEmpty()) {
      if (closed) {
        getContext().stop(getSelf());
      }
    } else {
      connection.tell(TcpMessage.write(storage.get(0), Ack.create(nextAck)), getSelf());
    }
  }

  private Receive closing() {
    return receiveBuilder()
        .match(
            Ack.class,
            ack -> {
              acknowledge(ack.ack);
            })
        .match(
            CommandFailed.class,
            failed -> {
              // write failed, retry
              connection.tell(failed.cmd(), getSelf());
            })
        .match(
            ConnectionClosed.class,
            closed -> {
              log.warning("Received {} closes after pending write(s) {}}", closed, storage.size());
              getContext().stop(getSelf());
            })
        .build();
  }

```

