SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/RetryFlow/withBackoff.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
val flow: Flow[Int, Int, NotUsed] = Flow[Int].map(x => if (x < 5) x else throw new RuntimeException("x too big"))

val retryFlow: Flow[Int, Int, NotUsed] = RetryFlow.withBackoff(
  minBackoff = 10.millis,
  maxBackoff = 5.seconds,
  randomFactor = 0.2,
  maxRetries = 5,
  flow
) { (in, out) =>
  out match {
    case Success(x) if x <= 0 => None // don't retry on 0 or negative values
    case Success(_)           => Some(in) // retry on positive values
    case Failure(_)           => Some(in) // retry on failure
  }
}
```

