TITLE: Initializing Akka Actor using message passing in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to initialize an Akka actor using message passing in Java. It uses the become method to transition between uninitialized and initialized states.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/actors.md#2025-04-22_snippet_47

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
static class InitializeMsg {
    public final String data;
    public InitializeMsg(String data) {
        this.data = data;
    }
}

static class Initialized {
    private final String data;
    public Initialized(String data) {
        this.data = data;
    }
    // getters, equals, hashCode
}

public static class InitializeViaMsgActor extends AbstractActor {
    private String initializeMe = null;

    @Override
    public Receive createReceive() {
        return receiveBuilder()
            .match(InitializeMsg.class, this::initializeMe)
            .match(String.class, this::replyIfInitialized)
            .build();
    }

    private void initializeMe(InitializeMsg msg) {
        initializeMe = msg.data;
        getContext().become(receiveBuilder()
            .match(String.class, this::replyIfInitialized)
            .build());
    }

    private void replyIfInitialized(String msg) {
        if ("get".equals(msg) && initializeMe != null)
            getSender().tell(new Initialized(initializeMe), getSelf());
    }
}
```

