TITLE: Defining Commands for a Counter Actor (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the command protocol for a simple counter actor using a Java interface `Command`. It includes commands for incrementing (`Increment`, `IncrementBy`) and retrieving the current value (`GetValue`, which includes an `ActorRef` for the reply).
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/durable-state/persistence.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
import akka.actor.typed.ActorRef;

interface Command {}

public enum Increment implements Command {
  INSTANCE
}

public static class IncrementBy implements Command {
  public final int value;

  public IncrementBy(int value) {
    this.value = value;
  }
}

public static class GetValue implements Command {
  public final ActorRef<State> replyTo;

  public GetValue(ActorRef<State> replyTo) {
    this.replyTo = replyTo;
  }
}

```

