TITLE: Applying a Sink to Substreams after groupBy in Java
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to apply a processing stage (a `Sink.fold` in this case, summing elements) independently to each substream created by the `groupBy` operator. The result of the fold for each substream is then ignored.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-substream.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
//#groupBy2
source
    .groupBy(2, element -> element % 2 == 0)
    .to(Sink.fold(0, (acc, i) -> acc + i))
    // From Sink.fold(0)(_ + _), even substream will emit 30 and odd 25
    // It means this will be applied independently for each substream
    .run(system);
//#groupBy2
```

