TITLE: Defining an Asynchronous Email Lookup Method (Java)
DESCRIPTION: Defines an asynchronous method `lookupEmail` that simulates looking up an email address for a given handle, returning a `CompletionStage<Optional<String>>`. It includes a simulated delay.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/futures-interop.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public static CompletionStage<Optional<String>> lookupEmail(String handle) {
  return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> {
    // simulate DB lookup
    System.out.println("Looking up email for " + handle);
    try {
      Thread.sleep(100);
    } catch (InterruptedException e) {
      Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
    }
    Optional<String> email;
    switch (handle) {
      case "rolandkuhn":
        email = Optional.of("rk@example.com");
        break;
      case "patriknw":
        email = Optional.of("pn@example.com");
        break;
      case "konradmalawski":
        email = Optional.of("km@example.com");
        break;
      default:
        email = Optional.empty();
    }
    System.out.println("Email for " + handle + ": " + email.orElse("None"));
    return email;
  });
}
```

