TITLE: Using Sink.ignore with Database Operations in Java
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use Sink.ignore in Java when reading lines from a file, saving them to a database, and storing the database identifiers in another file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Sink/ignore.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
// #ignore
Source<ByteString, CompletionStage<IOResult>> fileSource =
    FileIO.fromPath(Paths.get("lines.txt"));

Source<String, NotUsed> strings =
    fileSource
        .via(Framing.delimiter(ByteString.fromString("\n"), 1024))
        .map(bytes -> bytes.utf8String().trim());

Flow<String, Integer, NotUsed> databaseFlow =
    Flow.of(String.class).mapAsync(4, line -> saveToDatabase(line));

Sink<Integer, CompletionStage<IOResult>> idsFileSink =
    Flow.of(Integer.class)
        .map(id -> ByteString.fromString(id.toString() + "\n"))
        .toMat(FileIO.toPath(Paths.get("ids.txt")), Keep.right());

// run stream and ignore the outcome
strings.via(databaseFlow).to(Sink.ignore()).run(materializer);

// or alternatively
strings.via(databaseFlow).toMat(idsFileSink, Keep.right()).run(materializer);
// #ignore
```

