TITLE: Defining Tweet Data Model in Java
DESCRIPTION: Defines classes for representing tweets and authors in Java, used in the reactive tweets example.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-quickstart.md#2025-04-22_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
class Author {
  private final String handle;

  public Author(String handle) {
    this.handle = handle;
  }

  public String handle() {
    return handle;
  }
}

class Hashtag {
  private final String name;

  public Hashtag(String name) {
    this.name = name;
  }

  public String name() {
    return name;
  }
}

class Tweet {
  private final Author author;
  private final long timestamp;
  private final String body;

  public Tweet(Author author, long timestamp, String body) {
    this.author = author;
    this.timestamp = timestamp;
    this.body = body;
  }

  public Author author() {
    return author;
  }

  public long timestamp() {
    return timestamp;
  }

  public String body() {
    return body;
  }

  public Set<Hashtag> hashtags() {
    return Arrays.stream(body.split("\\s"))
        .filter(a -> a.startsWith("#"))
        .map(a -> new Hashtag(a.replaceAll("[^#\\w]", "")))
        .collect(Collectors.toSet());
  }
}
```

