TITLE: Using Sink.cancelled to Immediately Cancel a Stream in Scala
DESCRIPTION: In this example, a source generating numbers from 1 to 5 is connected to Sink.cancelled, which immediately cancels the stream and returns NotUsed as the materialized value, preventing any elements from being processed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Sink/cancelled.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
import akka.NotUsed
import akka.actor.ActorSystem
import akka.stream.scaladsl.{Sink, Source}

object CancelledExample {
  implicit val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem()

  def main(args: Array[String]): Unit = {
    // #cancelled
    // numbers will be produced until the stream is cancelled
    val cancelled: NotUsed =
      Source(1 to 5).runWith(Sink.cancelled)
    // #cancelled

    system.terminate()
  }
}
```

