TITLE: Implementing Lookup Classification Bus in Java
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of an EventBus using Lookup Classification, which maps events to subscribers based on event topics. It demonstrates efficient event classification and publishing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class LookupBusImpl extends EventBus<MsgEnvelope, String, ActorRef>
    implements LookupClassification {
  // is used for extracting the classifier from the incoming events
  @Override
  public String classify(MsgEnvelope event) {
    return event.topic;
  }

  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers which registered themselves
  // for the event's classifier
  @Override
  public void publish(MsgEnvelope event, ActorRef subscriber) {
    subscriber.tell(event.payload, ActorRef.noSender());
  }

  // must define the classifier to subscriber mapping
  @Override
  public int compareSubscribers(ActorRef a, ActorRef b) {
    return a.compareTo(b);
  }

  // must define how the mapping is stored
  @Override
  public <A> void mapSize() {
    return 128;
  }
}
```

