TITLE: Helper Functions for NACK-Based Write Back-Pressure in Scala
DESCRIPTION: Helper functions for the Scala EchoHandler implementation that support the back-pressure mechanism. These include specific states for handling acknowledgments and waiting for writing to resume.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/io-tcp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
def waitingForAck(buffer: Vector[ByteString]): Receive = {
  case WritingResumed =>
    if (buffer.nonEmpty) {
      connection ! Write(buffer.head, Ack)
      context.become(buffering(buffer.tail))
    } else {
      context.become(writing)
    }

  case Received(data) =>
    context.become(waitingForAck(buffer :+ data))

  case _: ConnectionClosed =>
    context.stop(self)
}

def waitingForAckAndClosing(reason: ConnectionClosed, buffer: Vector[ByteString]): Receive = {
  case WritingResumed =>
    if (buffer.nonEmpty) {
      connection ! Write(buffer.head, Ack)
      context.become(closing(reason, buffer.tail))
    } else {
      context.stop(self)
    }
}
```

