TITLE: Implementing Actor Lifecycle in Java
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to handle actor lifecycle events, specifically the PostStop signal, in Java.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/guide/tutorial_1.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
class StartStopActor1 {
  static Behavior<String> create() {
    return Behaviors.setup(
        context -> {
          System.out.println("first started");
          context.spawn(StartStopActor2.create(), "second");

          return Behaviors.receiveMessage(
              message -> {
                System.out.println("first received: " + message);
                return Behaviors.stopped();
              })
              .receiveSignal(
                  PostStop.class,
                  (context1, signal) -> {
                    System.out.println("first stopped");
                    return Behaviors.same();
                  });
        });
  }
}

class StartStopActor2 {
  static Behavior<String> create() {
    return Behaviors.setup(
        context -> {
          System.out.println("second started");

          return Behaviors.receiveSignal(
              PostStop.class,
              (context1, signal) -> {
                System.out.println("second stopped");
                return Behaviors.same();
              });
        });
  }
}
```

