TITLE: RoundRobin Class for Stateful Routing in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a RoundRobin class used for stateful routing in the PartitionHub example for Java. It maintains a counter to implement round-robin behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-dynamic.md#2025-04-22_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
class RoundRobin implements BiFunction<PartitionHub.ConsumerInfo, String, Long> {
  private int i = -1;

  @Override
  public Long apply(PartitionHub.ConsumerInfo info, String elem) {
    i++;
    long idx = info.consumerIds().get(i % info.size());
    return idx;
  }
}
```

