TITLE: Transforming Arithmetic Exceptions with mapError in Akka Streams (Java)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the mapError operator in Java to transform an ArithmeticException into a UnsupportedOperationException when the element 0 goes through a map operator that divides by the element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Source-or-Flow/mapError.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
import akka.actor.ActorSystem;
import akka.japi.function.Function;
import akka.stream.javadsl.*;
import java.util.Arrays;

ActorSystem system = ActorSystem.create("mapError-system");

Source<Integer> source = Source.from(Arrays.asList(0, 1, 2));
// #map-error
Source<Integer> stream =
    source
        .map(n -> 1 / n) // will throw ArithmeticException for n = 0
        .mapError(
            ArithmeticException.class,
            ex -> new UnsupportedOperationException("Operation not supported"));
// #map-error
```

