TITLE: Counting Tweets Using Fold in Akka Streams (Scala)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to count the number of tweets in a stream using Sink.fold. The result is made available as a Future[Int].
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/stream-quickstart.md#2025-04-22_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
val count: Flow[Tweet, Int, NotUsed] = Flow[Tweet].map(_ => 1)

val sumSink: Sink[Int, Future[Int]] = Sink.fold[Int, Int](0)(_ + _)

val counterGraph: RunnableGraph[Future[Int]] =
  tweets
    .via(count)
    .toMat(sumSink)(Keep.right)

val sum: Future[Int] = counterGraph.run()

sum.foreach(c => println(s"Total tweets processed: $c"))
```

