TITLE: Implementing an Actor That Supports Backpressure in Java
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of an actor that processes messages and acknowledges them to support backpressure. The actor handles various message types including stream elements, initialization, completion, and failure messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Sink/actorRefWithBackpressure.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
static class Ref extends AbstractActor {
  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
      .match(StreamInit.class, s -> {
        System.out.println("Stream initialized!");
        sender().tell(Continue.instance, self());
      })
      .match(StreamElement.class, s -> {
        System.out.println("Stream element: " + s.element);
        sender().tell(Continue.instance, self());
      })
      .match(StreamComplete.class, s -> {
        System.out.println("Stream completed!");
        context().stop(self());
      })
      .match(StreamFailure.class, s -> {
        System.out.println("Stream failed with: " + s.ex.getMessage());
        context().stop(self());
      })
      .build();
  }
}
```

