TITLE: Implementing Scanning Classification Bus in Java
DESCRIPTION: A Java implementation of an EventBus using Scanning Classification. It demonstrates processing each event by scanning through all subscribers and determining matches based on custom criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class ScanningBusImpl extends EventBus<String, String, ActorRef>
    implements ScanningClassification {
  // is needed for determining matching classifiers and subscribers
  @Override
  public boolean matches(String classifier, String event) {
    // publish String messages to subscribers that handle events starting with
    // the given classifier
    return event.startsWith(classifier);
  }

  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers
  @Override
  public void publish(String event, ActorRef subscriber) {
    subscriber.tell(event, ActorRef.noSender());
  }

  // may define the subscriber order which is used throughout the lifetime of the EventBus
  @Override
  public int compareSubscribers(ActorRef a, ActorRef b) {
    return a.compareTo(b);
  }

  // determines the initial size of the index data structure
  // used internally (i.e. the expected number of different classifiers)
  @Override
  public int mapSize() {
    return 128;
  }
}
```

