TITLE: Implementing Lookup Classification Bus in Scala
DESCRIPTION: A Scala implementation of an EventBus using Lookup Classification which maps from event type to a set of subscribers. This allows efficient subscriber lookup based on exact event type matching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/event-bus.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
class LookupBusImpl extends
  EventBus[MsgEnvelope, String, ActorRef] with LookupClassification {
  // is used for extracting the classifier from the incoming events
  override protected def classify(event: MsgEnvelope): String = event.topic

  // will be invoked for each event for all subscribers which registered themselves
  // for the event's classifier
  override protected def publish(event: MsgEnvelope, subscriber: ActorRef): Unit = {
    subscriber ! event.payload
  }
}
```

