TITLE: Selecting a Mailbox Type for an Actor in Java
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to select a specific mailbox for an actor using MailboxSelector to create a Props instance for actor spawning in Java.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/typed/mailboxes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
ActorRef<Command> boundedMailbox =
    context.spawn(
        behavior,
        "bounded-mailbox-actor",
        // create a bounded mailbox with a capacity of 100 messages and a default overflow strategy
        MailboxSelector.bounded(100));

ActorRef<Command> unboundedMailbox =
    context.spawn(
        behavior,
        "unbounded-mailbox-actor",
        // default is an unbounded mailbox, same as not specifying
        MailboxSelector.unbounded());

ActorRef<Command> fromConfig =
    context.spawn(
        behavior,
        "from-config-mailbox-actor",
        // select the mailbox-type from config
        MailboxSelector.fromConfig("my-app.my-special-mailbox"));
```

