TITLE: Creating Reactive Streams Publishers with Sink.asPublisher in Scala
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a Publisher from a Sink in Scala, showing the difference between fanout=true (allowing multiple subscribers) and fanout=false (allowing only the first subscriber).
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Sink/asPublisher.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Scala
CODE:
```
val source = Source(1 to 5)

// When fanout is set to true, multiple subscribers can attach to this publisher
val (publisherWithFanout, notUsed) = source.toMat(Sink.asPublisher(fanout = true))(Keep.both).run()

publisherWithFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-A"))
publisherWithFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-B"))
publisherWithFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithFanout-C"))

// Await for verification
// expect 5 elements for each of the three subscribers

// When fanout is set to false, the first subscriber will trigger publisher,
// and the rest will be rejected
val (publisherWithoutFanout, notUsed2) = source.toMat(Sink.asPublisher(fanout = false))(Keep.both).run()

publisherWithoutFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-A"))
publisherWithoutFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-B")) // will receive onError
publisherWithoutFanout.subscribe(createSubscriber("WithoutFanout-C")) // will receive onError

// Await for verification
// expect 5 elements for subscriber "WithoutFanout-A", but error for "WithoutFanout-B/C"
```

