TITLE: Using RetryFlow.withBackoffAndContext in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation example of RetryFlow.withBackoffAndContext with a FlowWithContext handling Integers with SomeContext, retrying elements based on output value and maxRetries conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/RetryFlow/withBackoffAndContext.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
FlowWithContext<Integer, SomeContext, Integer, SomeContext, NotUsed> flow =
    // business logic
    FlowWithContext.<Integer, SomeContext>create().map(i -> i - 1);

FlowWithContext<Integer, SomeContext, Integer, SomeContext, NotUsed> retryFlow =
    RetryFlow.withBackoffAndContext(
        Duration.ofMillis(10),
        Duration.ofSeconds(5),
        0.2,
        3,
        flow,
        (Pair<Integer, SomeContext> in, Pair<Integer, SomeContext> out) -> {
          if (out.first() <= 0) {
            // do not retry on 0 or negative
            return Optional.empty();
          } else if (in.first() - 1 == out.first()) {
            // do not retry on expected outcome
            return Optional.empty();
          } else {
            // otherwise retry with the original value
            return Optional.of(in);
          }
        });
```

