TITLE: Using Request Context with Get in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java example showing how to pass a request context (original sender) with a Get message, which can be used to route the response back to the original requester.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/distributed-data.md#2025-04-22_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
final Key<PNCounter> Counter1Key = PNCounterKey.create("counter1");
replicator.tell(
    new Get<>(Counter1Key, ReadLocal.instance(), getContext().getSender()), getSelf());

// handle response
receiveBuilder()
    .match(
        GetSuccess.class,
        g -> {
          if (g.key().equals(Counter1Key) && g.getRequest().isPresent()) {
            ActorRef replyTo = (ActorRef) g.getRequest().get();
            long value = ((PNCounter) g.dataValue()).getValue().intValue();
            replyTo.tell(value, getSelf());
          }
        })
    .match(
        NotFound.class,
        n -> {
          if (n.key().equals(Counter1Key) && n.getRequest().isPresent()) {
            ActorRef replyTo = (ActorRef) n.getRequest().get();
            replyTo.tell(new Integer(0), getSelf());
          }
        })
    .match(
        GetFailure.class,
        f -> {
          if (f.key().equals(Counter1Key) && f.getRequest().isPresent()) {
            ActorRef replyTo = (ActorRef) f.getRequest().get();
            replyTo.tell(new Integer(-1), getSelf());
          }
        })
    .build();
```

