TITLE: Restarting Source with Kill Switch in Java
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to stop the restarting of a source using a kill switch. The kill switch is inserted right after the restart source. The inner source emits 3 elements and then fails. A killswitch is used to be able to stop the source from being restarted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/RestartSource/onFailuresWithBackoff.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
Pair<UniqueKillSwitch, CompletionStage<Done>> stream =
    RestartSource.onFailuresWithBackoff(
            Duration.ofSeconds(1),
            Duration.ofSeconds(10),
            0.2,
            () ->
                Source.from(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4))
                    .map(
                        n -> {
                          if (n == 4) {
                            throw new RuntimeException("Boom!");
                          } else {
                            System.out.println(n);
                            return n;
                          }
                        }))
        .viaMat(KillSwitches.single(), Keep.right())
        .toMat(Sink.ignore(), Keep.both())
        .run(system);

// Stop the restarts:
stream.first().shutdown();
```

