TITLE: Implementing Stats Service in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation of the statistics service that receives text, splits it into words, delegates counting to worker routees via a cluster-aware router.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/cluster-routing.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
public class StatsService extends AbstractActor {

  @Override
  public void preStart() {
    // the service can re-used from several systems (Master/Worker)
    context().actorOf(Props.create(StatsWorker.class), "statsWorker");
  }

  // This router is used both with lookup and deploy of routees. If you
  // have a router with only lookup of routees you can use Props.empty
  // instead of Props.create(StatsWorker.class).
  private final ActorRef workerRouter = getContext().actorOf(
    FromConfig.getInstance().props(Props.create(StatsWorker.class)),
    "workerRouter");

  @Override
  public Receive createReceive() {
    return receiveBuilder()
      .match(StatsMessages.StatsJob.class, job -> {
        if (job.getText().equals(""))
          return;
        String[] words = job.getText().split("\\s+");

        // create actor that collects replies from workers
        ActorRef aggregator = getContext().actorOf(
          Props.create(StatsAggregator.class, words.length, getSender()));

        // send each word to a worker
        for (String word : words) {
          workerRouter.tell(new StatsMessages.ProcessWord(word), aggregator);
        }
      })
      .build();
  }

}
```

