TITLE: Stateful MapConcat Implementation Pattern in Java
DESCRIPTION: Java implementation showing how to combine statefulMap and mapConcat to implement statefulMapConcat-like behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Source-or-Flow/statefulMap.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
Source.from(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5))
    .statefulMap(
        () -> 0,
        (Integer state, Integer element) -> {
          ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
          for (int i = 0; i < state; i++) {
            list.add(element);
          }
          return new Pair<>(state + 1, list);
        },
        state -> Optional.empty())
    .mapConcat(ints -> ints);
```

