TITLE: Implementing UnfoldAsync Stream in Java
DESCRIPTION: Creates a stream of ByteStrings using unfoldAsync by repeatedly requesting chunks from an actor.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akka/akka/blob/main/akka-docs/src/main/paradox/stream/operators/Source/unfoldAsync.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public Source<ByteString, NotUsed> createSource(ActorRef actor) {
    return Source.unfoldAsync(
        0L,
        (Long offset) -> {
          CompletionStage<Chunk> fut =
              PatternsCS.ask(actor, new GetChunk(offset), Duration.ofSeconds(3))
                  .thenApply(resp -> (Chunk) resp);

          return fut.thenApply(
              chunk -> {
                if (chunk.getBytes().isEmpty())
                  return Optional.empty();
                else
                  return Optional.of(
                      new Pair<>(
                          offset + chunk.getBytes().length(),
                          chunk.getBytes()));
              });
        });
}
```

